Ethics

incremental: true Ethics of using the leaks - The new role of journalists, for better or for worse, isnt as gatekeepers, but interpreters: If they dont parse it, others without the experience, credentials, or mindfulness toward protecting personal information certainly will.

  • That hesitance, however, is at least in part responsible for the quality, and character, of much of the reporting thus far.

https://www.buzzfeed.com/annehelenpetersen/complicated-sony-ethics?s=mobile&utm_term=.psK9ZQew5#.uqNNk1Gq5

Some techy stuff sorry about that

incremental: true

  • Whats an email?
  • Formats : mbox, eml, maildir, pst

Some obvious infos that will lead the investigation :

  • Sender and receiver(s) : Quantify and qualify links between persons and entities
  • Body : Content and semantic analysis
  • Headers : Technical infos (like IP adresses, OS, Timestamp, etc.. ). Useful for context and verification of the leak
  • Attachments : Format? Type?

Different visualizations possible, for a good story

incremental: true

  • Geographical distribution (maps)
  • Relationship between people (Networks)
  • Stats on volumes, quantity, etc
  • Amounts on pro format and invoices in attachments
  • etc

Tools !!! Import, convert, export and parse

incremental: true - Grep - Ok this is hard beginning But it works! - Importing mails in thunderbird : ImportExportTools plugin
Please visit https://addons.mozilla.org/fr/thunderbird/addon/importexporttools/ Enhance TBs ability to bulk import mails. Export a mailbox in csv files! - Converting a pst file in eml files : libpst
Please visit http://www.five-ten-sg.com/libpst/
Simply type :

readpst -r Outlook.pst
  • Mailraider for OSX : https://www.45rpmsoftware.com/mailraider.php

Tools !!! Index search and tag

incremental: true - Overview Docs : The open source document mining platform
Please visit https://www.overviewdocs.com/
- OpenSemanticSearch Integrated research tools for easier searching, monitoring, analytics, discovery & text mining of heterogenous & large document sets & news with free software on your own server
Please visit https://www.opensemanticsearch.org/
- DocFetcher : Simple standalone yet efficient application for indexing and searching documents.
Please visit http://docfetcher.sourceforge.net/en/index.html - Bulkextractor : computer forensics tool that scans a disk image, a file, or a directory of files and extracts useful information
Please visit http://www.forensicswiki.org/wiki/Bulk_extractor

Tools !!! Just like beer, homebrewing

incremental: true - A mail parser using python https://github.com/SpamScope/mail-parser - Alexandres homebrew script using python (used on (cini) case ) - Mailbox-with-R, Hervs solution using R : available in this repo - Always think about Semantic Analysis :
Useful to Quickly evaluate the interest of a mailbox, the context
Useful to build homemade dictionaries to break passwords!
A nice R package : https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/tm.plugin.mail/tm.plugin.mail.pdf

Conclusion

incremental: true - Main difficulties :

  • Encoding sucks. I mean Really!
  • Low volume of emails available

  • Unique sender
    These two factors produce biases in interpretation

  • Really useful analysis!
